overview: The user initiated a review of their sleep questionnaire application,
  providing a detailed specification and Statement of Work. The agent conducted
  a comprehensive analysis, identifying several critical missing features and
  gaps in the existing implementation. Following this review, the agent
  proceeded to implement the identified high-priority items. This included
  integrating a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness, complete with safety warnings
  for high scores, adding detection logic for Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea
  (COMISA) and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, and incorporating a dedicated
  section for external resources and links within the generated reports. The
  implementation involved updating data types, validation schemas, UI
  components, and report generation logic for both web and PDF formats, ensuring
  the application now aligns more closely with the original requirements.
